All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
public class LayerCapabilities
extends Capabilities

Defines the capabilities for Layers. The simplest way to access a capability is to use one of the predefined capability indexes provided in this class, for example, to find out if a layer has caching, and if so, if caching is enabled, you could use code such as the following


       Layer layer;
       LayerCapabilities capabilities = layer.getCapabilities();
       Capability capability = capabilities.getCapability(LayerCapabilities.CACHING);
       if (capability.isOkToUse()()) {
           ....
       }

Field Detail

CACHING

public static final int CACHING
capabilities index for a layer caching capability. A Layer with this capability available can locally cache data from a server. When caching is available, calling code is allowed to enable or disable caching as desired, for example this might be appropriate for performing an attribute query that avoids the cache and directly queries the server.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATTRIBUTE_QUERY

public static final int ATTRIBUTE_QUERY
capabilities index for a attribute querying capability. A Layer with this capability available can respond to a search() where the QueryFilter specifies a list of subfields. This capability can sometimes be disabled as a result of some security reason, for example, ArcIMS SpatialServer can be administered to deny attribute queries through the use of Access Control Lists.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

SPATIAL_QUERY

public static final int SPATIAL_QUERY
capabilities index for a spatial querying capability. A Layer with this capability available can respond to a search() where the QueryFilter is a type of SpatialFilter. This capability can sometimes be disabled as a result of some security reason, for example, ArcIMS SpatialServer can be administered to deny spatial queries through the use of Access Control Lists.

Constructor Detail

LayerCapabilities

public LayerCapabilities()
Adds capabilities that are appropriate for Layers. All capabilities are initialized to be unavailable, disabled, and unable to be enabled/disabled. These capabilities are assumed to be appropriate for non-Dataset Layers, for example GroupLayer. Particular LayerSources are expected to adjust these as appropriate when constructing a Layer.
